Publication:
    https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4840234/
    
    "We developed the Genomic Regions Enrichment of Annotations Tool (GREAT) to analyze the functional significance 
    of cis-regulatory regions identified by localized measurements of DNA binding events across an entire genome."

Tutorial:
    https://davetang.org/muse/2014/05/16/genomic-regions-enrichment-of-annotations-tool/
    
    "In brief, GREAT is an alternative to gene-centric enrichment tools such as DAVID and uses a binomial test to test 
    for ontology enrichment."
